TheWord.Title: Odun Ohun, but Ohun fi ara mo.

JehovahRophe.Commentary: Jehovah Rophe. At Joppa, there is a certain disciple, Tabitha, which is by interpretation Dorcas. Tabitha is full of good works, alms deeds, and she makes coats and garments. When Tabitha will pass away, the disciples will send for Peter whom is at Lydda. But Peter will pray for Tabitha, and she will arise. Tabitha's resurrection will bring glory to the LORD God. Peter will stay many days at Joppa with Simon a tanner (Acts 9:36-40). Tabitha - James Strong Number 5000 (Act 9:36, 40).
